children.subject: How's the courseload of 182 relative to 186 or 161? How difficult is it in terms of homework and exams?

If you are interested in the more math side of things, definitely take both 126/127 during your last year. I would also recommend 162.

A lot of this depends on your interests, but I would say that I would prioritize 182 the least. A lot of 182’s material can be learned on your own and I think learning and doing the other courses you have listed will be more beneficial.

history.content:
Hi everyone, I am a Senior EECS major trying to decide what classes to pursue in the final year. I have taken 61A/B/C, 70, 170, Math 110, Data 100, 170, 186, 188 when it comes to CS-related classes. I am also trying to decide which one of 126 or 127 to do currently, and am enrolled in both.

This leaves me with one final semester to choose classes, and I am having issues deciding, as I am interested in quite a few - 182, 189, 162, 161, and whatever was left over from 126/127.

I ideally want to take three of them, perhaps one to broaden my understanding of ML and the others to give me a deeper general understanding of concepts. Does anyone have any recommendations on which to take next semester, and which to do between 126/127 this semester? 

Thanks a lot for the help!
history.subject: Course Recommendations for Final Semester
